commText: Prithvi Shaw and Warner are at the crease. Prithvi Shaw is on strike. Chahar will open the attack
Chahar to Prithvi Shaw, no run, starts with a gentle outswinger but keeps it tight around off stump, Prithvi flicks nicely but picks out mid-wicket

Chahar to Prithvi Shaw, 2 runs, oh sliced off a thickish edge, Prithvi was sucked into an off-side drive because of extra outswing, lost grip on the bat handle, ball runs along the ground through cover-point
Prithvi Shaw in IPL 2023 Inns: 8 Runs: 106 Avg: 13.25 SR: 124.7 50s: 1 HS: 54
Chahar to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, tried the inswinger there but didn't swing enough, length was slightly short too to allow Prithvi a back foot punch, backward point dives and gets a hand to save three

Chahar to Warner, no run, oh lazy poke! Warner was very late in deciding to have a late dab. Wanted to see if was shaped back in, was the away-going ball from good length, so he just tried to run it down to third man but got beaten
Deepak Chahar vs Prithvi Shaw in IPL 74 balls 85 runs 6 dismissals 14.17 avg 114.86 SR

Chahar to Warner, no run, inside edge onto pad! Again reacts a tad late as he tries the drive. Outswinger starting outside off stump, ball swings it to trouble him on the shot as he was trying to reach out

Chahar to Warner, FOUR, no problems in creaming this cover drive for four! Deepak Chahar overpitched this attempted outswinger outside off stump and Warner middled that to perfection. That will make him feel so good
Warner vs CSK in IPL Inns: 20 Runs: 644 Avg: 32.2 SR: 131.96 50s: 8 HS: 90
Tushar Deshpande, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

Tushar Deshpande to Prithvi Shaw, no run, edgeddd but doesn't carry! The lone skip for Tushar Deshpande and he squares up Prithvi on the defence. Perfect outswinger, was short of length, Prithvi tried to defend, soft hands saved him there as it dropped on its way to Jinks at slip
Tushar Deshpande to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, lovely short of length delivery slightly moving away, Prithvi gets the outside edge that rolls to third man
Tushar Deshpande to Warner, no run, check defence from Warner as he had to adjust to this inward movement from Tushar Deshpande. Seemed like it jumped on him too from good length
Tushar Deshpande to Warner, 1 run, oh again late on the shot! Full and swinging back in, Warner looks to slog, seems to be picking up swing pretty late, luckily the edge was thick edge
Tushar Deshpande to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, fullish delivery, Prithvi guides it to third man
Tushar Deshpande to Warner, no run, full delivery on the stumps, Warner drives it back to the bowler
Outstanding over from Tushar Deshpande. Great control over swing and line. Sedate start from DC
Chahar to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, wrists this outswinger to mid-on, sets off and gets home before the direct-hit from Rachin
Chahar to Warner, SIX, he's had enough of this tight bowling. Bends his knees to get under this length delivery and hit with the swing over backward square leg for a handsome six. Lovely hit that!
Chahar to Warner, no run, back to bowling just outside off stump, Warner pushes it to cover
Chahar to Warner, no run, clever short delivery angling away from the left-hander, Warner had to take the risk of fetching the pull and he let it go to avoid the trap

Chahar to Warner, 2 runs, oh follows up with a really full delivery that rushes Warner on the flick as he had to clear his front leg out. Chipped just wide of mid-on and fielder slides to save two at the fence
Chahar to Warner, no run, pace off full delivery, Warner drives gently to mid-off. Good comeback after that six from Chahar
Tushar Deshpande to Prithvi Shaw, no run, oh hit that drive very nicely down the ground but Tushar Deshpande stuck his right hand out to save a certain four
Tushar Deshpande to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, and there's the thrash from Prithvi. Fullish and outside off stump, Prithvi square drives in the air, hits it fiercely for four
Third man and deep square now

Tushar Deshpande to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, mistimes the drive on the rise, seems like ball isn't coming on as expected, luckily the ball clears Rutu to the left at mid-off. Usually these on the rise punches from Prithvi disappear
Tushar Deshpande to Warner, no run, 116.8kph full slower delivery wide of off stump, Warner reaches out and taps it to point
Tushar Deshpande to Warner, no run, inside edge onto pad! Missed out on a freebie there. Full and on middle and leg, flick was on but he tried to hit it too square and missed out on a few runs
Tushar Deshpande to Warner, no run, what an outstanding yorker aiming base of middle and off, Warner digs it out to point. Two gun overs from Tushar Deshpande
Chahar to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, 115kph length slower ball, Prithvi pulls to deep mid-wicket but there is protection in the deep, cut off to the left

Chahar to Warner, 2 runs, now the slower ball bumper, Warner rolls his wrists to keep the early pull on the ground to the left of short fine leg and he steals the second run. Brilliant running. Fizz lacked fizz there but the angle was tough to cut for him
Chahar to Warner, SIX, overdoes the slower delivery! This time 116.6kph and leg-side, Warner waits and picks it up behind square and clears the fence so easily
Chahar to Warner, FOUR, now the pace on low full toss, Warner pounces on it to thump it through cover. Deepak Chahar losing it this over. He's winning the battle for being patient

Chahar to Warner, FOUR, and he continues! Again the short slower delivery but with width, Warner waits and cuts over point and give more life into this innings. Great counterattack and calucated assault on a bowler to better the powerplay
Chahar to Warner, 1 run, loses shape on the slog, inside edge to mid-on and he keeps strike
Deep backward square and third man for Fizz
Mustafizur Rahman, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mustafizur to Warner, FOUR, Warner is in full flow now! WIdth on offer outside off stump from Fizz and Warner cuts fiercely through point. He scored 19 runs off the last 5 balls
Mustafizur to Warner, no ball, leg byes, 1 run, really full delivery troubles Warner, but the buzzer is off and it's a front foot no ball. Prithvi Shaw gets to face the free-hit
Mustafizur to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, goes for the yorker but fires down leg. Prithvi glances it past short fine leg for four. What a turnaround for DC
Mustafizur to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, and how smart of Prithvi to get inside the line and glance really fine with control past the man at short fine leg

Mustafizur to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, make that a hat-trick of fours for Prithvi Shaw! This is the best shot of the lot. Short of a length delivery angling away, Prithvi punches it off the back foot, sweet timing through cover-point
Mustafizur to Prithvi Shaw, byes, 1 run, beaten by the slower delivery angling across, bounces awkwardly for Dhoni and he puts he wears it on the chest to stop the ball. Warner meanwhile steals a run
Mustafizur to Warner, 1 run, slower delivery outside off stump, Warner drives square of the wicket on the off-side

Powerplay summary -- First four overs - 24 runs, next two go for 38 -- Warner, Shaw take flight after steady start -- Chahar taken for 18 in 5th over -- Mustafizur goes for 18 in 6th over -- Runs start to flow after new ball stops swinging

DC force an early timeout for CSK by plundering 38 runs off the last 2 PP overs. Tushar bowled great two overs, but Deepak Chahar lost it after a good start and Fizz wasn't disciplined. DC would be really upbeat about this wicketless start and this is the combination they wanted for the openers
Ravindra Jadeja, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Jadeja to Warner, 1 run, turning back in, bit of turn on offer, Warner flicks this flighted delivery through backward square leg

Jadeja to Prithvi Shaw, SIX, Jadeja overcooks this flighted delivery and Prithvi smacks the slog-sweep. He wanted to toss this up for a mishit, but the length was too full and paid the price. Prithvi middled that so well
Jadeja to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, now goes back and pulls to deep square leg

Jadeja to Warner, FOUR, pulls in the air but wide of Mitchell at deep backward square leg. Shortish from Jadeja, Warner goes back and plays the shot, places it well to get the boundary to the left of the fielder
Jadeja to Warner, no run, punches it towards cover-point
Warner vs Jadeja in T20s (before today) 124 runs 69 balls no dismissal 179.71 SR 4s/6s: 6/9
Jadeja to Warner, 1 run, flighted delivery on the stumps, Warner flicks to long-on
Matheesha Pathirana, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Pathirana to Warner, no ru, oh he smacked that cut shot but picked out backward point. That was a certain four! Width outside off stump from Pathirana and Warner middled that nicely
Pathirana to Warner, 1 run, full and down leg, Warner flicks through backward square leg
Pathirana to Prithvi Shaw, no run, short delivery outside off stump, Prithvi looks to guide it to third man and misses
Pathirana to Prithvi Shaw, wide, this bouncer is too high says the ump as it goes past Prithvi's attempted ramp
Pathirana to Prithvi Shaw, wide, now the off-side wide as he tries to hide the ball
Pathirana to Prithvi Shaw, no run, full and wide of off stump, Prithvi tries to reach out for the drive, inside edge rolls to the on-side
Pathirana to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, fullish delivery, Prithvi pushes it to mid-off for a quick single
Pathirana to Warner, leg byes, 1 run, slower delivery dow leg, Warner misses the glance, ball rolls to fine leg off the pad. Good over from Pathirana despite two wides, just 4 off it
Jadeja to Warner, SIX, Jadeja overpitches again and Warner smacks this over wide long-on. Flighted delivery outside off stump, slot ball and Warner won't miss out on these freebies!
Jadeja to Warner, 1 run, short and outside off stump, Warner cuts to deep backward point. Prithvi Shaw was keen for two but sent back
Seems like Warner is struggling because of hot humid conditions. Asks one of his teammates to pour some water on his face
Jadeja to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, turning away, Prithvi punches it to long-on
Jadeja to Warner, 1 run, flighted delivery on the stumps, Warner flicks to mid-wicket and that's lovely fifty - 62nd in IPL for Davey Warner. Raises hit bat to acknowledge the applause
Jadeja to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, pushed off the back foot to long-off
Jadeja to Warner, 1 run, shortish delivery, Warner pulls off the bottom of the bat to deep mid-wicket. He seems to be tiring
Most 50+ scores in T20 cricket 110 - David Warner* 110 - Chris Gayle 101 - Virat Kohli 98 - Babar Azam 86 - Jos Buttler
Mustafizur Rahman [1.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack

Mustafizur to Warner, 1 run, dropped! Slower delivery, Warner smashes it down the ground, Fizz was moving to his right in his followthrough, ball goes to his left, sticks his left hand out and no way he was going to catch those, real toughie! Ball deflects and just misses the stumps, Prithvi Shaw was outside the crease and he escapes the runout but it hits umpire Kumar Dharmasena on the foot and they all share a smile
Mustafizur to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, worked away to mid-wicket
Mustafizur to Warner, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mustafizur to Warner, out Caught by Pathirana!! Baby Malinga! Those slingers have helped him stretch his right hand really far back to pluck off this one-hander. Warner can't believe he's out to ball that he feels is a hit-me ball. Slower and full, Warner shapes up for the reverse-lap and actually hits it decently well, just that the placement wasn't right. Pathirana dives to his right and catches it behind his body. Ball just stucks in his fingertips. Prithvi pats Warner on the head as he walks off. End of a fine innings and the bowling change has worked for CSK. Warner c Pathirana b Mustafizur 52(35) [4s-5 6s-3]
Rishabh Pant, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Mustafizur to Pant, no run, thuds the pad by beating the flick but it was heading down leg
Warner's last five scores vs CSK 57(55) 19(12) 0(2) 86(58) 52(35) - today
Mustafizur to Pant, 1 run, pushed towards point
Last four opening stands for DC vs CSK 16(11) 0(2) 5(9) 93(58) - today
Mustafizur to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, slower delivery, Prithvi wrists this to mid-wicket
Two four-run overs killing the momentum for DC
Rishabh Pant vs CSK in IPL (before today) Inns: 10 Runs: 324 Avg: 46.28 SR: 156.52 50s: 2 HS: 79
Jadeja to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, flighted delivery on the stumps, Prithvi works it to mid-wicket
Jadeja to Pant, 1 run, fired flat and fast outside off stump to take it out of Pant's arc, flat-batted pull to long-on

Jadeja to Prithvi Shaw, SIX, another slog-sweep and he nails it well enough. Not as full as the previous six he had off Jaddu, had to kind of reach out but he put on a bold face to go through with the shot without minding the top edge and he clears the mid-wicket rope
Jadeja to Prithvi Shaw, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Jadeja to Prithvi Shaw, out Caught by Dhoni!! Oh thick edge and MSD has held it! That wasn't an easy catch at all. Quicker delivery spinning away, Prithvi looks to cut, big deflection and Dhoni held his hands soft enough for the ball to nicely cushion into the gloves. Prithvi walks off without waiting for the finger. DC lose both set batters in quick succession. Prithvi will feel happy about that knock on return to the team. Prithvi Shaw c Dhoni b Jadeja 43(27) [4s-4 6s-2]
Most dismissals by a WK in T20s 300 - MS Dhoni* 274 - Kamran Akmal 274 - Dinesh Karthik 270 - Quinton de Kock 209 - Jos Buttler
Mitchell Marsh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Jadeja to Mitchell Marsh, 1 run, slider down leg, Marsh works it to mid-on
Jadeja to Pant, no run, beaten! Pant tries the reverse sweep and loses shape, ball slides past everything. Jaddu interested for a catch but MSD wasn't
Tushar Deshpande [2.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Mitchell Marsh, 1 run, Mitchell flicks this short of length delivery to deep backward square leg
Tushar Deshpande to Pant, no run, pace off, Pant misses the flick and gets hit on the pad
Tushar Deshpande to Pant, 1 run, on the leg stump, Pant flicks through backward square leg
Tushar Deshpande to Mitchell Marsh, no run, short slower delivery outside off stump, Marsh lets it go
Tushar Deshpande to Mitchell Marsh, wide, oh that was a hit me low full toss down leg, Marsh misses the glance
Tushar Deshpande to Mitchell Marsh, no run, oh uppish defence as this seems to have stopped on the batter

Tushar Deshpande to Mitchell Marsh, FOUR, lovely hit! Mid-off up and it's a full slot ball, easy hit for Marsh and he doesn't try to overhit. Just a neat lofted off-drive to get the boundary they were desperate for
Jadeja to Pant, 2 runs, oh man at backward point dives to save two runs. Was cut well as Pant used width on this ball
Jadeja to Pant, no run, wide of off stump, Pant slices it towards backward point
Jadeja to Pant, SIX, changes the angle and goes round the wicket but bowls close to Pant's body and out comes a lovely slog-sweep over mid-wicket
Jadeja to Pant, no run, shortish delivery, Pant cuts and finds backward point again
Jadeja to Pant, 1 run, back over the wicket for a dart outside off stump, Pant cuts square of the wicket to deep point
Jadeja to Mitchell Marsh, 1 run, on the leg stump, Marsh works it to short mid-wicket and that's the end of Jaddu with the ball for the day
Deepak Chahar [3.0-0-34-0] is back into the attack
Chahar to Mitchell Marsh, no run, pace off delivery, stump-lined. Marsh waits and then pushes it tamely towards extra cover
Chahar to Mitchell Marsh, 1 run, once again pace off and hits the deck hard, Marsh with a bit of a shimmy forwards tries a big swipe across the line. Underedges it towards deep backward square leg
Chahar to Pant, no run, 117 clicks, back of length and angling across, gets a bit of extra bounce and goes over Pant's attempted cut shot
Chahar to Pant, no run, fuller delivery angling towards middle and off, Pant gets low on one leg and tries to ramp it but hits it faintly towards short fine

Chahar to Pant, 1 run, pace off, length and wide. Pant throws the kitchen sink at it but skews his timing completely. Flies off the outer half and the bat flies off his hands as well. On the bounce towards deep point

Chahar to Mitchell Marsh, SIX, brute power from the big Australian!! Just 117 clicks, back of length delivery on off. Marsh stays back expecting that length and heaves it over deep square into the stands. Deepak Chahar has a day to forget!

Summary (Overs 7-14) -- 67/2 -- Scoring rate drops as both openers depart -- Pathirana takes a screamer to get rid of Warner for 52 (9.3) -- Jadeja gets rid of Shaw for 43 (10.4) -- Jadeja bowls out with 1/43 -- Chahar bowls out with 0/42 -- Pant struggling for rhythm
Matheesha Pathirana [1.0-0-4-0] is back into the attack
Pathirana to Pant, 1 run, full delivery near the boots, Pant flicks it towards deep mid-wicket. On the bounce towards the fielder
Pathirana to Mitchell Marsh, no run, hard length and the slingy action makes it angle away outside off. Punched into the ground towards covers

Pathirana to Mitchell Marsh, FOUR, 144 clicks, back of length delivery on the body. Marsh with a swivel pull that goes behind square and thuds onto the hoardings before the fielders could even react!!
Pathirana to Mitchell Marsh, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Pathirana to Mitchell Marsh, out Bowled!! Fast bowling at its finest!! To outdo an Aussie batter who's grown up on the wickets of Perth for pace shows how good a delivery that would have been from Matheesha Pathirana. 150 clicks, on the money with the yorker and rattles the stumps before the batter could get his bat down to block. Gets a bit of inward movement as well on that one, unplayable stuff!! Mitchell Marsh b Pathirana 18(12) [4s-2 6s-1]
Tristan Stubbs, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Pathirana to Tristan Stubbs, no run, 149.5 clicks, full delivery outside off, Stubbs can't connect on the drive
Pathirana to Tristan Stubbs, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Pathirana to Tristan Stubbs, out Bowled!! Another one!! Another out of this world yorker from Matheesha Pathirana. And this time it castles a South African who's no newcomer to speed. 149.5 clicks, fast and knocks down the off and middle pole. Sri Lankan cricket, you have your successor to Malinga. His name is Matheesa Pathirana! A game changing over from the youngster Tristan Stubbs b Pathirana 0(2)

Tushar Deshpande to Pant, no run, good length and angling across, slapped towards extra cover
Tushar Deshpande to Pant, wide, too far wide outside off
Tushar Deshpande to Pant, 2 runs, good length and straighter, pulled towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs
Tushar Deshpande to Pant, 1 run, a well delivered wide yorker from Deshpande. Pant stabs it out square of the wicket
Tushar Deshpande to Axar, 1 run, good length delivery onto the thigh pad, clipped towards fine leg
Tushar Deshpande to Pant, no run, now a good bouncer from Deshpande, angling across. Pant tried to upper cut it but couldn't get bat on it

Tushar Deshpande to Pant, FOUR, attempted wide yorker that ends as a low full toss, Pant throws his bat at it and the bottom hand comes off it. However, the connection is clean enough on the drive as the ball flies to the left of the deep point fielder. Couple of bounces and four

Time-Out. Those two superb yorkers from Pathirana have firmly tilted this game in favour of CSK. Delhi need a strong finish in these slog overs now to have any chance on this really good looking batting surface. Their skipper Rishabh Pant has his eye in after playing 20 balls, is today the day he can burst back into the scene?
Pathirana to Axar, 1 run, full and straight, Axar turns his bat on the drive towards long-on
Pathirana to Pant, 1 run, 149.8 clicks, fuller delivery that is angling across, catches an edge and goes towards short third. The fielder fumbles slightly to allow the single
Pathirana to Axar, 1 run, wide yorker from Pathirana, run down towards third-man
Pathirana to Pant, 1 run, another wide yorker from Pathirana, stabbed out towards cover point
Pathirana to Axar, 1 run, 136.2 clicks, fuller delivery outside off, squeezed square of the wicket for the fifth single of the over

Pathirana to Pant, no run, 147.5 clicks, nails the wide yorker! Pant late on getting his bat down to guide it down towards third. What a great spell of fast bowling this has been from Matheesha Pathirana. 3-0-14-2 so far
Mustafizur Rahman [2.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
Mustafizur to Axar, 1 run, back of length and angling inwards, was the cutter. Dabbed towards backward point for a single
Mustafizur to Pant, FOUR, short ball angling inwards to Pant. He swivel pulls it away towards the deep square leg boundary. Wasn't the pretiest of shots, but gets the result he would have wanted
Mustafizur to Pant, 1 run, wide yorker, Pant tried to get under it on the slog. Hits it into the pitch towards mid-wicket
Mustafizur to Axar, byes, 1 run, pace off full delivery outside off, Axar goes for a big slog but plays the wrong line. Dhoni can't collect that cleanly, parries it towards short fine

Mustafizur to Pant, SIX, a vintage one-handed flick that sails about 20 rows back beyond the deep backward square leg boundary!! Mustafizur goes fuller and onto middle and leg, Pant rolls back time on him!!

Mustafizur to Pant, 1 run, low, wide full toss. Pant tried to get under it and smoke it down the ground. Connected off the toe-end and on the bounce towards long-on. Still, a productive over - 14 runs off it
Pathirana to Pant, 2 runs, length ball onto middle stump, Pant goes for a big heave across the line. Inside halves it towards the right of deep mid-wicket

Pathirana to Pant, SIX, what a hit!! Slightly undercooked on the yorker and that was enough for Rishabh Pant to get under it. Manufactures the room for himself to get a clean bat swing and slams it to the left of long-on for a flat six!!
Pathirana to Pant, FOUR, six followed by four!! Once again not too much wrong with the yorker but Pant manages to get under it and clear his front leg to slam it down the ground for a boundary

Pathirana to Pant, FOUR, a fifty of great nostalgic and emotional value perhaps for Rishabh Pant, DC fans and India fans!! First fifty since his comeback and it comes off 31 balls. A wide yorker from Matheesha Pathirana, Pant slices his drive behind square for a boundary
Pathirana to Pant, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Pathirana to Pant, out Caught by Gaikwad!! Fifty and out!! A yorker length delivery onto off, Pant tried to get under it but this time toe-ends it high in the air. Felt like it might land safe but Ruturaj runs in from long-off and takes a solid, tumbling catch. Third wicket for Pathirana. Pant c Gaikwad b Pathirana 51(32) [4s-4 6s-3]
Abishek Porel, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Pathirana to Abishek Porel, 1 run, full on the pads, clipped towards deep backward square leg

Mustafizur to Abishek Porel, no run, 138.5 clicks, wide yorker from Mustafizur. Porel tried to stab it behind square but can't connect. Given wide by the umpire but CSK review and it was the right side of the blue line, umpire forced to reverse decision.
Mustafizur to Abishek Porel, FOUR, goes wide yorker once again, this time Porel gets his bat down and opens the bat face to squeeze it to the right of short third for a boundary
Mustafizur to Abishek Porel, wide, too wide this time outside off on the yorker
Mustafizur to Abishek Porel, no ball, 1 run, low full toss, Porel can't get under it and slams it down to long-on. However, Mustafizur has overstepped! Freehit coming up
Mustafizur to Axar, 1 run, low full toss on off stump, Axar inside edges it onto his pads and scampers for the single. Mustafizur gets off cheaply on the freehit
Mustafizur to Abishek Porel, 2 runs, shuffles all the way across to ramp this wide yorker over the short fine fielder. However, it will be cut off by the deep square leg fielder
Mustafizur to Abishek Porel, 1 run, low, wide full toss. Porel drives it in front of square. Looked good for a couple but Sameer Rizvi jolts to his left from sweeper cover to save a run
Mustafizur to Axar, 1 run, wide yorker, stabbed out square of the wicket for a single. Delhi Capitals end on 191 runs.

21:15 Local Time, 15:45 GMT, 21:15 IST: A late slog overs dash from Rishabh Pant has helped the Delhi Capitals end on 191 runs, but they might perhaps be a few runs short on this track against an attack minded CSK batting line-up. The Capitals openers started tepidly, negating the early swing and going at a run a ball for the first four overs. However, Warner flipped the switch in the third Deepak Chahar over as he took him down for two fours and a six. Shaw followed that up next over with four consecutive boundaries against Mustafizur. However, Chennai wrestled back the momentum with a couple of quiet overs post the powerplay, and that forced Warner to try a reverse ramp against Mustafizur. That proved to be his undoing as the southpaw perished shortly after his fifty thanks to a worldie catch from Pathirana. Shaw was out next over, with MS taking a sharp catch behind the wickets. Things stumbled in the middle overs for DC, as Pathirana bowled two superb yorkers to knock over Marsh and Stubbs. It looked like DC would amble to a sub par total post those two jolts, but skipper Rishabh Pant found some of his old form back as he plundered 17 runs off Pathirana's last over, notching up his first fifty since his comeback. 43 runs off the final three overs have helped the Capitals end on a good score, but will it be enough? Back shortly for the chase.

David Warner: Probably what we have got is ideal, but 200 would have been fantastic. We lost two wickets in the middle and the way Rishabh came out and played was phenomenal. He (Prithvi) has been working very hard, to see him hit cleanly was fantastic. Hard lengths into the wicket and off pace stuck and held on the pitch. We got to hit the stumps as much as we can and get the fields right and make sure we bowl to that.
Ready for the chase. Khaleel with the new ball, two slips in place. The two Aussies in the cordon, Marsh at a wide fourth slip type position. Let's play!!
